 (set of machines) and (away from cities) development: ideas from a Grameen 
 Bank village phone effort in Bangladesh* 
 Abdul Bayes* 
 Jahangirnagar University, Savm; Dhaka, Bangladesh 
 
 Abstract 
 The plan/purpose of the present paper is to test the role of (related to sending and receiving phone calls, texts, etc.) within the contexts of (away from cities) development in 
 general and of poorness reduction especially. Bangladesh has been selected as a case study due to the (quality of being unlike anything else in the world) it displayed 
 in an new and interesting program for expanded telecom (set of machines), in which Grameen Bank (GB) of Bangladesh, the village-based 
 micro-finance organisation, leased cellular mobile phones to successful members. GB calls these phones village pay phones 
 (VPPs). The effects ofVPPs are tested from two angles: sellers of services (telephone lessees/owners) and buyers of services 
 (villagers). The findings of the study lead to two basic ends/end results: first, (trying to reach the goal of/trying to complete the requirements of) practical policies can turn telephones 
 into production products (that are bought and sold), especially through lowering transaction costs, and second, the services starting from telephones in 
 villages are likely to deliver (even) more benefits to the poor than to the non-poor. The VPPs also seem to have visible and 
 positive effects on the permission and social status of phone-leasing women and their families. For villagers in general, 
 phones offer added/more non-money-based benefits such as improved police, more fast and effective communications 
 during disasters, stronger relationship (gluing or joining together/friendship forming), etc. GB's style of managing communications can help significantly to expand 
 access to this important  information input for all segments of people/of the group, reduce (state where two things are not the same) and so improve the broad-based, 
 pro-poor (direction of pointing/way of thinking/information meeting) of (away from cities) development activities.Â© 2001 Elsevier Science B.V. All rights reserved. 
 Keywords: (related to sending and receiving phone calls, texts, etc.) technology; Microfinance; Grameen Bank; (away from cities) development; (male/female status) 
 
