 poor group deal with money-based and health (things to carefully think about). 
 
 4. The effects of village pay phones 
 4.1. Money-based effects 
 4.1.1. Net profit ofVPP owners 
 As was explained above, the GB leased phones to 
 its most successful members in the target villages. 
 The goal was to add to household income, 
 rather than replace it (at least over the short term). 
 As is the case with other business activities, the net 
 (money made/good thing received) (accomplished or gained) on telephone services equals total receipts/revenues from sales minus total costs incunÂ·ed 
 to (understand/make real/achieve) these sales. To calculate the net (money made/good thing received) earned 
 from selling phone services, the following formula was 
 used: 
 
